4781 // Compares the name of each test with the user-specified filter to
4782 // decide whether the test should be run, then records the result in
4783 // each TestCase and TestInfo object.
4784 // If shard_tests == true, further filters tests based on sharding
4785 // variables in the environment - see
4786 // http://code.google.com/p/googletest/wiki/GoogleTestAdvancedGuide.
4787 // Returns the number of tests that should run.
4788 int UnitTestImpl::FilterTests(ReactionToSharding shard_tests) {
4789  const Int32 total_shards = shard_tests == HONOR_SHARDING_PROTOCOL ?
4790  Int32FromEnvOrDie(kTestTotalShards, -1) : -1;
4791  const Int32 shard_index = shard_tests == HONOR_SHARDING_PROTOCOL ?
4792  Int32FromEnvOrDie(kTestShardIndex, -1) : -1;
4793 
4794  // num_runnable_tests are the number of tests that will
4795  // run across all shards (i.e., match filter and are not disabled).
4796  // num_selected_tests are the number of tests to be run on
4797  // this shard.
4798  int num_runnable_tests = 0;
4799  int num_selected_tests = 0;
4800  for (size_t i = 0; i < test_cases_.size(); i++) {
4801  TestCase* const test_case = test_cases_[i];
4802  const std::string &test_case_name = test_case->name();
4803  test_case->set_should_run(false);
4804 
4805  for (size_t j = 0; j < test_case->test_info_list().size(); j++) {
4806  TestInfo* const test_info = test_case->test_info_list()[j];
4807  const std::string test_name(test_info->name());
4808  // A test is disabled if test case name or test name matches
4809  // kDisableTestFilter.
4810  const bool is_disabled =
4811  internal::UnitTestOptions::MatchesFilter(test_case_name,
4812  kDisableTestFilter) ||
4813  internal::UnitTestOptions::MatchesFilter(test_name,
4814  kDisableTestFilter);
4815  test_info->is_disabled_ = is_disabled;
4816 
4817  const bool matches_filter =
4818  internal::UnitTestOptions::FilterMatchesTest(test_case_name,
4819  test_name);
4820  test_info->matches_filter_ = matches_filter;
4821 
4822  const bool is_runnable =
4823  (GTEST_FLAG(also_run_disabled_tests) || !is_disabled) &&
4824  matches_filter;
4825 
4826  const bool is_selected = is_runnable &&
4827  (shard_tests == IGNORE_SHARDING_PROTOCOL ||
4828  ShouldRunTestOnShard(total_shards, shard_index,
4829  num_runnable_tests));
4830 
4831  num_runnable_tests += is_runnable;
4832  num_selected_tests += is_selected;
4833 
4834  test_info->should_run_ = is_selected;
4835  test_case->set_should_run(test_case->should_run() || is_selected);
4836  }
4837  }
4838  return num_selected_tests;
4839 }

4841 // Prints the given C-string on a single line by replacing all '\n'
4842 // characters with string "\\n". If the output takes more than
4843 // max_length characters, only prints the first max_length characters
4844 // and "...".
4845 static void PrintOnOneLine(const char* str, int max_length) {
4846  if (str != NULL) {
4847  for (int i = 0; *str != '\0'; ++str) {
4848  if (i >= max_length) {
4849  printf("...");
4850  break;
4851  }
4852  if (*str == '\n') {
4853  printf("\\n");
4854  i += 2;
4855  } else {
4856  printf("%c", *str);
4857  ++i;
4858  }
4859  }
4860  }
4861 }

4863 // Prints the names of the tests matching the user-specified filter flag.
4864 void UnitTestImpl::ListTestsMatchingFilter() {
4865  // Print at most this many characters for each type/value parameter.
4866  const int kMaxParamLength = 250;
4867 
4868  for (size_t i = 0; i < test_cases_.size(); i++) {
4869  const TestCase* const test_case = test_cases_[i];
4870  bool printed_test_case_name = false;
4871 
4872  for (size_t j = 0; j < test_case->test_info_list().size(); j++) {
4873  const TestInfo* const test_info =
4874  test_case->test_info_list()[j];
4875  if (test_info->matches_filter_) {
4876  if (!printed_test_case_name) {
4877  printed_test_case_name = true;
4878  printf("%s.", test_case->name());
4879  if (test_case->type_param() != NULL) {
4880  printf(" # %s = ", kTypeParamLabel);
4881  // We print the type parameter on a single line to make
4882  // the output easy to parse by a program.
4883  PrintOnOneLine(test_case->type_param(), kMaxParamLength);
4884  }
4885  printf("\n");
4886  }
4887  printf(" %s", test_info->name());
4888  if (test_info->value_param() != NULL) {
4889  printf(" # %s = ", kValueParamLabel);
4890  // We print the value parameter on a single line to make the
4891  // output easy to parse by a program.
4892  PrintOnOneLine(test_info->value_param(), kMaxParamLength);
4893  }
4894  printf("\n");
4895  }
4896  }
4897  }
4898  fflush(stdout);
4899 }

4936 // Shuffles all test cases, and the tests within each test case,
4937 // making sure that death tests are still run first.
4938 void UnitTestImpl::ShuffleTests() {
4939  // Shuffles the death test cases.
4940  ShuffleRange(random(), 0, last_death_test_case_ + 1, &test_case_indices_);
4941 
4942  // Shuffles the non-death test cases.
4943  ShuffleRange(random(), last_death_test_case_ + 1,
4944  static_cast<int>(test_cases_.size()), &test_case_indices_);
4945 
4946  // Shuffles the tests inside each test case.
4947  for (size_t i = 0; i < test_cases_.size(); i++) {
4948  test_cases_[i]->ShuffleTests(random());
4949  }
4950 }

4997 // If *pstr starts with the given prefix, modifies *pstr to be right
4998 // past the prefix and returns true; otherwise leaves *pstr unchanged
4999 // and returns false. None of pstr, *pstr, and prefix can be NULL.
5000 bool SkipPrefix(const char* prefix, const char** pstr) {
5001  const size_t prefix_len = strlen(prefix);
5002  if (strncmp(*pstr, prefix, prefix_len) == 0) {
5003  *pstr += prefix_len;
5004  return true;
5005  }
5006  return false;
5007 }

5009 // Parses a string as a command line flag. The string should have
5010 // the format "--flag=value". When def_optional is true, the "=value"
5011 // part can be omitted.
5012 //
5013 // Returns the value of the flag, or NULL if the parsing failed.
5014 const char* ParseFlagValue(const char* str,
5015  const char* flag,
5016  bool def_optional) {
5017  // str and flag must not be NULL.
5018  if (str == NULL || flag == NULL) return NULL;
5019 
5020  // The flag must start with "--" followed by GTEST_FLAG_PREFIX_.
5021  const std::string flag_str = std::string("--") + GTEST_FLAG_PREFIX_ + flag;
5022  const size_t flag_len = flag_str.length();
5023  if (strncmp(str, flag_str.c_str(), flag_len) != 0) return NULL;
5024 
5025  // Skips the flag name.
5026  const char* flag_end = str + flag_len;
5027 
5028  // When def_optional is true, it's OK to not have a "=value" part.
5029  if (def_optional && (flag_end[0] == '\0')) {
5030  return flag_end;
5031  }
5032 
5033  // If def_optional is true and there are more characters after the
5034  // flag name, or if def_optional is false, there must be a '=' after
5035  // the flag name.
5036  if (flag_end[0] != '=') return NULL;
5037 
5038  // Returns the string after "=".
5039  return flag_end + 1;
5040 }

5042 // Parses a string for a bool flag, in the form of either
5043 // "--flag=value" or "--flag".
5044 //
5045 // In the former case, the value is taken as true as long as it does
5046 // not start with '0', 'f', or 'F'.
5047 //
5048 // In the latter case, the value is taken as true.
5049 //
5050 // On success, stores the value of the flag in *value, and returns
5051 // true. On failure, returns false without changing *value.
5052 bool ParseBoolFlag(const char* str, const char* flag, bool* value) {
5053  // Gets the value of the flag as a string.
5054  const char* const value_str = ParseFlagValue(str, flag, true);
5055 
5056  // Aborts if the parsing failed.
5057  if (value_str == NULL) return false;
5058 
5059  // Converts the string value to a bool.
5060  *value = !(*value_str == '0' || *value_str == 'f' || *value_str == 'F');
5061  return true;
5062 }

5098 // Determines whether a string has a prefix that Google Test uses for its
5099 // flags, i.e., starts with GTEST_FLAG_PREFIX_ or GTEST_FLAG_PREFIX_DASH_.
5100 // If Google Test detects that a command line flag has its prefix but is not
5101 // recognized, it will print its help message. Flags starting with
5102 // GTEST_INTERNAL_PREFIX_ followed by "internal_" are considered Google Test
5103 // internal flags and do not trigger the help message.
5104 static bool HasGoogleTestFlagPrefix(const char* str) {
5105  return (SkipPrefix("--", &str) ||
5106  SkipPrefix("-", &str) ||
5107  SkipPrefix("/", &str)) &&
5108  !SkipPrefix(GTEST_FLAG_PREFIX_ "internal_", &str) &&
5109  (SkipPrefix(GTEST_FLAG_PREFIX_, &str) ||
5110  SkipPrefix(GTEST_FLAG_PREFIX_DASH_, &str));
5111 }

5113 // Prints a string containing code-encoded text. The following escape
5114 // sequences can be used in the string to control the text color:
5115 //
5116 // @@ prints a single '@' character.
5117 // @R changes the color to red.
5118 // @G changes the color to green.
5119 // @Y changes the color to yellow.
5120 // @D changes to the default terminal text color.
5121 //
5122 // TODO(wan@google.com): Write tests for this once we add stdout
5123 // capturing to Google Test.
5124 static void PrintColorEncoded(const char* str) {
5125  GTestColor color = COLOR_DEFAULT; // The current color.
5126 
5127  // Conceptually, we split the string into segments divided by escape
5128  // sequences. Then we print one segment at a time. At the end of
5129  // each iteration, the str pointer advances to the beginning of the
5130  // next segment.
5131  for (;;) {
5132  const char* p = strchr(str, '@');
5133  if (p == NULL) {
5134  ColoredPrintf(color, "%s", str);
5135  return;
5136  }
5137 
5138  ColoredPrintf(color, "%s", std::string(str, p).c_str());
5139 
5140  const char ch = p[1];
5141  str = p + 2;
5142  if (ch == '@') {
5143  ColoredPrintf(color, "@");
5144  } else if (ch == 'D') {
5145  color = COLOR_DEFAULT;
5146  } else if (ch == 'R') {
5147  color = COLOR_RED;
5148  } else if (ch == 'G') {
5149  color = COLOR_GREEN;
5150  } else if (ch == 'Y') {
5151  color = COLOR_YELLOW;
5152  } else {
5153  --str;
5154  }
5155  }
5156 }

5251 #if GTEST_USE_OWN_FLAGFILE_FLAG_
5252 void LoadFlagsFromFile(const std::string& path) {
5253  FILE* flagfile = posix::FOpen(path.c_str(), "r");
5254  if (!flagfile) {
5255  fprintf(stderr,
5256  "Unable to open file \"%s\"\n",
5257  GTEST_FLAG(flagfile).c_str());
5258  fflush(stderr);
5259  exit(EXIT_FAILURE);
5260  }
5261  std::string contents(ReadEntireFile(flagfile));
5262  posix::FClose(flagfile);
5263  std::vector<std::string> lines;
5264  SplitString(contents, '\n', &lines);
5265  for (size_t i = 0; i < lines.size(); ++i) {
5266  if (lines[i].empty())
5267  continue;
5268  if (!ParseGoogleTestFlag(lines[i].c_str()))
5269  g_help_flag = true;
5270  }
5271 }
5272 #endif // GTEST_USE_OWN_FLAGFILE_FLAG_

5274 // Parses the command line for Google Test flags, without initializing
5275 // other parts of Google Test. The type parameter CharType can be
5276 // instantiated to either char or wchar_t.
5277 template <typename CharType>
5278 void ParseGoogleTestFlagsOnlyImpl(int* argc, CharType** argv) {
5279  for (int i = 1; i < *argc; i++) {
5280  const std::string arg_string = StreamableToString(argv[i]);
5281  const char* const arg = arg_string.c_str();
5282 
5283  using internal::ParseBoolFlag;
5284  using internal::ParseInt32Flag;
5285  using internal::ParseStringFlag;
5286 
5287  bool remove_flag = false;
5288  if (ParseGoogleTestFlag(arg)) {
5289  remove_flag = true;
5290 #if GTEST_USE_OWN_FLAGFILE_FLAG_
5291  } else if (ParseStringFlag(arg, kFlagfileFlag, &GTEST_FLAG(flagfile))) {
5292  LoadFlagsFromFile(GTEST_FLAG(flagfile));
5293  remove_flag = true;
5294 #endif // GTEST_USE_OWN_FLAGFILE_FLAG_
5295  } else if (arg_string == "--help" || arg_string == "-h" ||
5296  arg_string == "-?" || arg_string == "/?" ||
5297  HasGoogleTestFlagPrefix(arg)) {
5298  // Both help flag and unrecognized Google Test flags (excluding
5299  // internal ones) trigger help display.
5300  g_help_flag = true;
5301  }
5302 
5303  if (remove_flag) {
5304  // Shift the remainder of the argv list left by one. Note
5305  // that argv has (*argc + 1) elements, the last one always being
5306  // NULL. The following loop moves the trailing NULL element as
5307  // well.
5308  for (int j = i; j != *argc; j++) {
5309  argv[j] = argv[j + 1];
5310  }
5311 
5312  // Decrements the argument count.
5313  (*argc)--;
5314 
5315  // We also need to decrement the iterator as we just removed
5316  // an element.
5317  i--;
5318  }
5319  }
5320 
5321  if (g_help_flag) {
5322  // We print the help here instead of in RUN_ALL_TESTS(), as the
5323  // latter may not be called at all if the user is using Google
5324  // Test with another testing framework.
5325  PrintColorEncoded(kColorEncodedHelpMessage);
5326  }
5327 }
5328 
5329 // Parses the command line for Google Test flags, without initializing
5330 // other parts of Google Test.
5331 void ParseGoogleTestFlagsOnly(int* argc, char** argv) {
5332  ParseGoogleTestFlagsOnlyImpl(argc, argv);
5333 }
5334 void ParseGoogleTestFlagsOnly(int* argc, wchar_t** argv) {
5335  ParseGoogleTestFlagsOnlyImpl(argc, argv);
5336 }

5338 // The internal implementation of InitGoogleTest().
5339 //
5340 // The type parameter CharType can be instantiated to either char or
5341 // wchar_t.
5342 template <typename CharType>
5343 void InitGoogleTestImpl(int* argc, CharType** argv) {
5344  // We don't want to run the initialization code twice.
5345  if (GTestIsInitialized()) return;
5346 
5347  if (*argc <= 0) return;
5348 
5349  g_argvs.clear();
5350  for (int i = 0; i != *argc; i++) {
5351  g_argvs.push_back(StreamableToString(argv[i]));
5352  }
5353 
5354  ParseGoogleTestFlagsOnly(argc, argv);
5355  GetUnitTestImpl()->PostFlagParsingInit();
5356 }

5358 } // namespace internal

5360 // Initializes Google Test. This must be called before calling
5361 // RUN_ALL_TESTS(). In particular, it parses a command line for the
5362 // flags that Google Test recognizes. Whenever a Google Test flag is
5363 // seen, it is removed from argv, and *argc is decremented.
5364 //
5365 // No value is returned. Instead, the Google Test flag variables are
5366 // updated.
5367 //

5370 #if defined(GTEST_CUSTOM_INIT_GOOGLE_TEST_FUNCTION_)
5371  GTEST_CUSTOM_INIT_GOOGLE_TEST_FUNCTION_(argc, argv);

5373  internal::InitGoogleTestImpl(argc, argv);
5374 #endif // defined(GTEST_CUSTOM_INIT_GOOGLE_TEST_FUNCTION_)
5375 }
